The paper discusses a method for finding satisfying assignments for variables involved in a set of constraints, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves lazy grounding of the theory during search, which is a technique used in logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of inductive definitions, which is a topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL) and data structures (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.AI, cs.LO, and cs.PL, followed by cs.CL and cs.DS.
